      • getAggregateFunction

        KsqlAggregateFunction<?,?,?> getAggregateFunction(FunctionName functionName,
                                                  SqlType argumentType,
                                                  AggregateFunctionInitArguments initArgs)
        Get an instance of an aggregate function.

        The current assumption is that all aggregate functions take a single argument for computing the aggregate at runtime. For functions that have no runtime arguments pass DEFAULT_FUNCTION_ARG_SCHEMA for the argumentType parameter.

        Some aggregate functions also take initialisation arguments, e.g. SELECT TOPK(AGE, 5) FROM PEOPLE.

        In the above 5 is an initialisation argument which needs to be provided when creating the KsqlAggregateFunction instance.

        Parameters:
        functionName - the name of the function.
        argumentType - the schema of the argument.
        Returns:
        the function instance.
        Throws:
        KsqlException - on unknown UDAF, or on unsupported argumentType.
